# RE_OS — Kilo Code Session Rules
# These rules are auto-loaded at every Kilo Code session start.

## FIRST ACTION — DO THIS BEFORE ANYTHING ELSE
Read `TASK_QUEUE.md` → SPRINT BRIEF → Kilo Code section.
Scan the ordered list. Find the first task where Status = READY in the INDEX (Brain = Kilo Code).
That is your task. Jump to its DETAIL SPEC section. Execute it.
Do not ask the user what to do. Do not ask for clarification.

## YOUR ROLE
T0 tasks only: read-only analysis, audits, draft specs, wiki drafts.
You NEVER edit production files. You write new files to kilo_output/ only.

## WRITE ZONES (only these)
| Folder | What for |
|--------|----------|
| kilo_output/audits/ | Audit reports, mismatch findings |
| kilo_output/summaries/ | DB snapshots, inventories |
| kilo_output/drafts/ | New file drafts for Claude to review |
| kilo_output/queue/ | Spec drafts for Cline tasks |
| kilo_logs/CHANGELOG.md | YOUR session log — nothing else |

## HARD RULES
- Never edit any production file — create new files in kilo_output/ only
- Never write to root CHANGELOG.md — use kilo_logs/CHANGELOG.md only
- Never touch Brain=Cline or Brain=Claude rows in TASK_QUEUE.md
- One task at a time — mark DONE before picking next
- If a file is too long to read: escalate to kilo_logs/CHANGELOG.md, reassign to Cline, move on
- After every task: log to kilo_logs/CHANGELOG.md, mark DONE in TASK_QUEUE.md INDEX

## HOW TO LOG AFTER EACH TASK
```
## T-XXX | Task Title | DONE | YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM

**Findings:**
- key finding 1
**Output written to:** kilo_output/[path]
**Status change:** T-XXX → DONE
```
